		<description><![CDATA[I am not one for going to networking events at all. I know everyone says you need to network, blah, blah, blah. I just find it so forced, wandering around a room introducing yourself to people. So it was quite a surprise that I enjoyed myself so much at last night&#8217;s The eMeet event in [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I am not one for going to networking events at all. I know everyone says you need to network, blah, blah, blah. I just find it so forced, wandering around a room introducing yourself to people. So it was quite a surprise that I enjoyed myself so much at last night&#8217;s <a href="http://www.theemeet.co.uk" target="_blank">The eMeet</a> event in Ronnie Scotts in Soho.</p>
<p>I was only there for the free booze (and that I try and expose myself to <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_swan_theory" target="_blank">black swans</a>), after an invite from the good people of <a href="http://www.viagogo.co.uk" target="_blank">Viagogo</a>, but managed to make some new contacts by accident after being subjected to people who were there to work the room and press the flesh.  Of the people I had never heard of but seemed to be involved in something interesting were Robin Dhara of <a href="http://www.red-robin.co.uk" target="_blank">Red Robin</a>, Rebekah Campbell from <a href="http://www.posse.com" target="_blank">Posse</a> (who&#8217;s site and domain name are excellent) and Marc Bridgen from <a href="http://www.gigjunkie.net" target="_blank">Gig Junkie</a>.</p>
<p>The eMeet is free to attend as long as you have registered beforehand and there&#8217;s space. It&#8217;s aimed at eCommerce people, although the definition of eCommerce People according to The eMeet&#8217;s Steve Roest, is anyone making money online. There was a definite bias towards music sites, probably because Roest also works for Viagogo, so there was a good fit with the night&#8217;s sponsor <a href="http://www.emusic.com" target="_blank">eMusic</a>, who I thought had ceased to exist!</p>
<p>I&#8217;ll definitely be attending in future, make sure you get in touch with the organisers and secure your place.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
